    <para id="id10384331">The advantage of the Pauling electronegativity scale is that it allows the prediction of general behavior. For example, the larger the difference in electronegativity between two elements the more ionic character or more polar the bonding interaction. Thus, a H-O bond (3.5 - 2.1 = 1.4) is more polar than a H-S bond (2.5 – 2.1 = 0.4). </para>
    
